<recipe>
<title>
Summer Vegetable Ragu
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 lb . eggplant peeled, in 1-inch pieces
1 c . sweet onion diced
2 T . olive oil
5 cloves garlic peeled and minced
1 oz can whole peeled tomatoes 28 .
fresh basil and grated Parmesan cheese for garnishing
</ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add eggplant and onion, and season with salt and pepper.
Cook until eggplant is lightly browned and onions are translucent, about 10 minutes.
Stir in garlic, and cook, stirring constantly, for 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes, and stir to combine.
Lightly crush tomatoes against the side of the skillet.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are warm, about 3-4 minutes.
Serve over pasta or polenta, and garnish with fresh basil and Parmesan just before serving.
</instructions>
</recipe>
